WEBVTT

00:11.359 --> 00:14.144
You're training
to be a priest?
I am.

00:14.188 --> 00:15.798
Also, an assessor.

00:15.841 --> 00:17.278
My colleague Ben and I are hired

00:17.321 --> 00:18.888
by the Church to investigate

00:18.931 --> 00:19.758
unexplained phenomenon,

00:19.802 --> 00:21.238
and to recommend whether

00:21.282 --> 00:23.197
there should be an exorcism
or further research.

00:23.240 --> 00:25.590
Possession looks a lot
like insanity.

00:25.634 --> 00:28.376
Insanity looks a lot
like possession.

00:28.419 --> 00:30.397
I need someone to help me
distinguish between the two.

00:30.421 --> 00:31.770
I don't believe in all that.

00:31.814 --> 00:32.771
Devils and possession.

00:32.815 --> 00:34.164
That's okay.

00:34.208 --> 00:35.861
You don't care
that I don't believe?

00:35.905 --> 00:37.254
I do not.

00:37.298 --> 00:39.039
We came into
an opportunity overnight.

00:39.082 --> 00:41.998
Another forensic psychologist.
You're just gonna overturn

00:42.042 --> 00:43.869
everything I did
on those two cases?

00:43.913 --> 00:47.221
Argue to release the guilty,
imprison the innocent? Yeah.

00:47.264 --> 00:50.137
Here's the most important thing
to remember about David:

00:50.180 --> 00:52.922
he sells himself
as this good man,

00:52.965 --> 00:55.925
but ask him about
the second time he saw God.

00:55.968 --> 00:57.840
This guy Townsend, you know him?

00:57.883 --> 00:59.798
- I've seen him.
- In other... guises.

00:59.842 --> 01:03.193
I'm sorry. Am I
distracting you?

01:06.936 --> 01:09.069
There are six types
of possession.

01:09.112 --> 01:10.722
First is demonic possession.

01:10.766 --> 01:12.637
It's when a demon takes over
a person's body

01:12.681 --> 01:13.856
without their consent.

01:13.899 --> 01:15.205
It's what you see
in most movies.

01:15.249 --> 01:18.121
It involves speaking in tongues,

01:18.165 --> 01:19.905
sudden personality changes,
sudden violence,

01:19.949 --> 01:21.342
even superhuman strength.

01:23.692 --> 01:26.651
The next type of possession
is physical pain.

01:26.695 --> 01:29.176
This is a sickness
or an injury due to a demon

01:29.219 --> 01:30.525
being inside a person.

01:30.568 --> 01:33.876
It doesn't impact the soul,
just the body.

01:33.919 --> 01:36.139
The third
is diabolic oppression.

01:36.183 --> 01:38.185
This is when a demon torments
a person,

01:38.228 --> 01:40.361
causing tragic events
in their lives...

01:40.404 --> 01:42.232
The loss of a loved one,

01:42.276 --> 01:44.147
the loss of a job,

01:44.191 --> 01:45.366
a home.

01:45.409 --> 01:47.281
Basically, the story of Job.

01:47.324 --> 01:50.458
The fourth type of possession
is diabolical infestation.

01:50.501 --> 01:53.069
It's when demonic entities
take over a house,

01:53.113 --> 01:54.679
an object,

01:54.723 --> 01:57.291
even an animal.

01:57.334 --> 01:59.554
Fifth is diabolical subjugation.

01:59.597 --> 02:01.382
It's when the possessed
invites the demon

02:01.425 --> 02:03.166
into their lives.

02:03.210 --> 02:04.733
They do this through game play

02:04.776 --> 02:06.430
or pledging their soul
to the devil.

02:06.474 --> 02:07.779
That's a real thing?

02:07.823 --> 02:09.389
People pledging their souls?

02:09.433 --> 02:11.392
It's real in that if a human
wants power,

02:11.435 --> 02:14.395
they can trade away their future
for that power.

02:14.438 --> 02:15.502
Oh, so you mean it as metaphor?

02:15.526 --> 02:17.267
No, I think a lot
of what we consider

02:17.311 --> 02:19.356
metaphor is real.

02:21.445 --> 02:23.404
Are you texting?

02:23.447 --> 02:24.492
No, I'm taking notes.

02:24.535 --> 02:26.363
Um, and the last
kind of possession?

02:26.407 --> 02:27.930
That's why we're here.

02:27.973 --> 02:29.845
The monsignor wants us to look
into a case

02:29.888 --> 02:31.412
of diabolical obsession.

02:31.455 --> 02:33.022
It's when a person has constant,

02:33.065 --> 02:34.893
overwhelming
and irrational thoughts,

02:34.937 --> 02:36.678
making them act
in perverse ways.

02:38.114 --> 02:39.724
It's hard to detect because
it's the most

02:39.768 --> 02:41.683
highly functional
of all the possessions.

02:41.726 --> 02:43.859
But it can lead to
suicidal ideation.

02:43.902 --> 02:45.252
And murder.

02:45.295 --> 02:46.446
I mean,
couldn't all these conditions

02:46.470 --> 02:48.168
have a psychological
explanation?

02:48.211 --> 02:51.258
Sure. That's why you're here.

02:51.301 --> 02:54.435
Ready? Yep. I'm ready.

02:56.480 --> 02:58.613
He wasn't like this before.

02:58.656 --> 03:01.093
I mean, he's always been
hard on us, cruel even,

03:01.137 --> 03:04.271
but he's become... violent.

03:04.314 --> 03:07.361
I don't know what to do.
We've tried everything:

03:07.404 --> 03:09.580
therapy, pills, So... Sorry,
I-I don't understand.

03:09.624 --> 03:12.409
Is this your husband? Oh, no.
He's my boss.

03:12.453 --> 03:15.195
Patti is one of our
best parishioners.

03:15.238 --> 03:17.434
I told her we could
look into it. BEN: So you think your boss

03:17.458 --> 03:19.155
