34:20.319 --> 34:22.973
You tell me what you remember
of his side of the conversation,

34:23.016 --> 34:25.106
and I duplicate it.

34:25.150 --> 34:29.110
You duplicate...
You can, you can do that?

34:29.154 --> 34:32.157
Yeah, I can, yeah.

34:34.202 --> 34:38.076
Look, if you don't want to,
it's totally... No, no, I...

34:38.119 --> 34:39.728
You can just create
a conversation?

34:39.773 --> 34:43.342
No, I-I wouldn't be creating it,
I would be recreating it.

34:43.385 --> 34:45.126
Look, it's-it's a conversation

34:45.170 --> 34:48.172
that you had and you lost,
and now you just want it back.

34:51.480 --> 34:53.221
If the ethics
of this throw you...

34:53.264 --> 34:57.269
No, no, I-I want it. I just...

35:02.056 --> 35:03.449
Yes, please do it.

35:16.201 --> 35:17.941
Sebastian Lewin.

35:17.985 --> 35:19.421
Yeah. What's the problem?

35:19.465 --> 35:21.293
That depends.

35:25.471 --> 35:26.950
I was just teaching
him a lesson.

35:26.994 --> 35:28.865
Yeah? By hacking
his virtual assistant?

35:28.909 --> 35:31.955
Yeah. He didn't pay for my work,
so I used his cell phone

35:31.999 --> 35:34.654
to slingshot my voice
onto his machine.

35:34.697 --> 35:36.438
You convinced him
to pledge his soul?
Yeah.

35:36.482 --> 35:39.615
And he believed me.
What a moron.

35:39.659 --> 35:42.531
So, uh, how'd you hack
my virtual assistant at home?

35:42.575 --> 35:44.098
What are you talking about?

35:44.142 --> 35:46.318
Your voice...
It was on my dad's machine.

35:46.361 --> 35:47.884
No.

35:47.928 --> 35:50.757
Yes, it was. I heard it.

35:50.800 --> 35:53.107
No, I stopped a few days ago.

36:09.428 --> 36:11.952
I don't believe you. JOE: Yes, you do.

36:11.995 --> 36:14.084
Iblis has your baby.

36:28.838 --> 36:30.840
What is that about?

36:34.279 --> 36:36.890
Karima.

36:36.933 --> 36:39.240
What is that about a baby?

36:41.286 --> 36:44.114
Karima!

37:10.315 --> 37:12.186
Mr. Duke, I am so sorry.

37:12.230 --> 37:13.579
This is a lemon poppy seed,

37:13.622 --> 37:15.320
and I'm not sure
how that happened...

37:15.363 --> 37:17.452
No, no, no, leave it. I'm fine.

37:17.496 --> 37:19.585
But it's lemon poppy seed.Yes.

37:19.628 --> 37:23.197
I'm expanding my horizons.
Leave it.

37:23.241 --> 37:25.939
You know, this experience has...

37:25.982 --> 37:28.289
Changed me? Oh, God, I hope not.

37:28.333 --> 37:32.032
Oh, whoops,
used the Lord's name in vain.

37:35.165 --> 37:37.385
Do you want me to start
rolling calls?

37:37.429 --> 37:38.908
Please.

37:38.952 --> 37:41.346
Sure.

37:47.352 --> 37:50.180
♪ Hell is only half full

37:50.224 --> 37:54.010
♪ Room for you and me

37:54.054 --> 37:57.187
♪ Looking for a new fool

37:57.231 --> 38:00.930
♪ Who's it gonna be?

38:00.974 --> 38:04.586
No, he's been good.
Very good, actually.

38:04.630 --> 38:08.329
I'm glad, but call the monsignor
if you have any more issues.

38:08.373 --> 38:11.506
I will. Yes. Oh, and can you
tell your partner

38:11.550 --> 38:14.422
that I have five tickets
for her for the new play?

38:14.466 --> 38:16.424
Thank you all.

38:16.468 --> 38:19.209
It's been a breath
of fresh air here.

38:19.253 --> 38:21.386
He hasn't fired anyone.

38:21.429 --> 38:22.865
He's even talked about hiring

38:22.909 --> 38:25.128
some of the other
assistants back.

38:25.172 --> 38:28.044
Yes. I don't know what you did,

38:28.088 --> 38:31.613
but it's a whole new world
around here.

38:39.317 --> 38:40.535
Ah, Dr. Townsend.

38:40.579 --> 38:43.973
Would you return
to the stand, please?

38:44.017 --> 38:46.236
Of course, Your Honor.

39:02.688 --> 39:03.906
A reminder, Doctor,

39:03.950 --> 39:07.388
you are still
under oath.
May I,

39:07.432 --> 39:09.869
Your Honor?

39:09.912 --> 39:11.610
Ah, Kristen.

39:11.653 --> 39:15.353
Can't stay away from me,
can you?

39:15.396 --> 39:16.484
What do you want to say?

39:16.528 --> 39:18.399
Why are you doing this to Adam?

39:18.443 --> 39:21.184
What good could
it possibly do you?

39:21.228 --> 39:26.015
Adam is a lightweight of clay
yet to find its form.

39:26.059 --> 39:28.235
Real prison will help mold him
into a man.

39:28.278 --> 39:30.585
It'll harden him.

39:30.629 --> 39:33.109
Do you recognize those words?

39:33.153 --> 39:35.329
That is your voice,
Doctor, isn't it?

39:35.373 --> 39:38.288
Again, Your Honor, objection.
This is a secret recording.

39:38.332 --> 39:40.029
Yes, and we are in
a one-party state,

39:40.073 --> 39:41.291
and we are using it to rebut

39:41.335 --> 39:42.771
an expert witness, Your Honor.

39:42.815 --> 39:46.209
Yes, Mr. Cormier, this is merely
a pre-trial hearing.

39:48.211 --> 39:50.126
Dr. Townsend, is
this your voice?

39:50.170 --> 39:53.042
It is not.
Really?

39:53.086 --> 39:54.653
Well, what about this?

39:54.696 --> 39:57.220
Why don't you just
get back on the stand

39:57.264 --> 39:59.353
and tell the truth?

39:59.397 --> 40:01.181
What are you trying to do,

40:01.224 --> 40:03.139
play on my better nature,
Kristen?

40:03.183 --> 40:05.098
Seriously.

40:05.141 --> 40:06.447
Is that really your plan?

40:06.491 --> 40:07.970
Look, he's just a kid.

40:08.014 --> 40:09.894
The second prison rape,
and he won't be anymore.

40:12.845 --> 40:15.369
So, Mr. Townsend,
what do you mean by that?

40:17.458 --> 40:21.157
That's Dr. Townsend.

40:22.158 --> 40:23.856
Thank you, Kristen.

40:25.292 --> 40:27.250
Still a long way to go.

40:27.294 --> 40:30.340
At least we have
a fighting chance now.

40:30.384 --> 40:31.646
Yes.

40:31.690 --> 40:34.083
Thank you so much.

40:38.871 --> 40:42.701
A deepfake... how very modern.
Those are my tools.

40:42.744 --> 40:45.355
What did Shakespeare say?

40:45.399 --> 40:48.489
"To do a great right,
do a little wrong."

40:48.533 --> 40:50.709
Technology's a bitch.

40:53.363 --> 40:55.322
You know the next line?

40:55.365 --> 40:58.760
"And curb this cruel devil
of his will."

40:58.804 --> 41:03.373
There are forces in play,
Kristen Bouchard.

